If you do not have brew installed just head to https://brew.sh/
Rest is self explantory on the website page.

But still if you insist

What is Homebrew?
It is a package manager for MacOS(& Linux).
If you dont have a software, just brew it!
It is based on git and ruby.
It insalls all the packages in its own folder and just creates symlinks in /usr/local

How to install brew?
(As mentioned on the website) 
Just execute the below on your terminal.
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install.sh)"

How to use it?
Just type 
brew install <software>

eg:
brew install git
brew install wget
brew install maven
brew install gradle

Good to know Commands : 

- To know all the commands run the below on your terminal.
brew commands

- Let the package speak for itself.
Type brew in terminal and hit enter. You will have the list and usage.
bash-3.2$ brew
Example usage:
  brew search [TEXT|/REGEX/]
  brew info [FORMULA...]
  brew install FORMULA...
  brew update
  
  brew upgrade [FORMULA...]
  brew uninstall FORMULA...
  brew list [FORMULA...]

Troubleshooting:
  brew config
  brew doctor
  brew install --verbose --debug FORMULA

Contributing:
  brew create [URL [--no-fetch]]
  brew edit [FORMULA...]

Further help:
  brew commands
  brew help [COMMAND]
  man brew
  https://docs.brew.sh
bash-3.2$ 

Uninstallation 
Although the article topic says how to install brew, but for some reason (space?) if you do wish to uninstall brew
ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/uninstall)"